id: pm-1etl
title: Clarify or harden SDK import resolution for local extension installs
description: Dogfood extension install from local path failed to load when extension imported @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk without its own dependency install.
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[4]: extensions,external-audit,pm-cli,sdk
created_at: "2026-04-25T23:06:27.563Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T20:02:40.225Z"
author: audit-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: Local extension install path provides deterministic guidance (or runtime support) for SDK import resolution and doctor output points directly to remediation.
parent: pm-o7be
comments[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-25T23:06:27.563Z",audit-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search 'audit extension sdk calendar docs' --mode keyword --limit 10; pm list-open --fields id,title,type,parent,status,priority --limit 50; pm list-in-progress --fields id,title,type,parent,status,priority --limit 50. Net-new because active items cover extension runtime probe/docs parity but not local install SDK module-resolution behavior."
  "2026-04-25T23:07:38.813Z",audit-agent,"Repro evidence from sandbox audit: local extension install succeeds, but doctor reports extension_load_failed when extension entry imports @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk and source package has no installed dependency. Runtime error: Cannot find package '@unbrained/pm-cli' imported from installed extension index.js."
  "2026-04-26T00:31:11.473Z",codex-agent,"Follow-up evidence from 2026-04-26 audit: local extension imports of @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk require ESM package metadata type module in addition to dependency installation. Without type module, extension install appears successful but runtime command path remains unavailable with only a Node module warning. Recommend install-time or doctor diagnostics that explicitly call out missing ESM package type alongside dependency guidance."
  "2026-04-26T08:42:53.552Z",codex-agent,Latest sandbox run confirms @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk imports work when extension package metadata and module setup are correct. Remaining ergonomics gap is actionable diagnostics when extension appears installed but runtime command remains unavailable due packaging mismatch; doctor guidance can be more direct.
  "2026-04-26T19:58:29.442Z",codex-agent,"Documentation hardening landed via docs/SDK.md and starter-extension package/README examples, reducing ambiguity around extension dependency setup for @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk imports."
  "2026-04-26T19:58:45.877Z",codex-agent,"Issue remains open for runtime diagnostics parity: extension doctor/install paths should emit clearer actionable errors when package metadata/module mode mismatch causes installed commands to remain unavailable."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-25T23:07:42.346Z",audit-agent,"Potential remediation paths: (a) install-time dependency validation/warning for local sources, (b) extension loader resolution fallback to pm CLI SDK for explicit compatibility mode, or (c) tighter doctor remediation hints with concrete npm install guidance."
files[4]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/examples/starter-extension/package.json,project,reference dependency wiring for @unbrained/pm-cli sdk imports
  docs/SDK.md,project,sdk quick-start now clarifies public sdk contract usage
  src/cli/commands/extension.ts,project,extension install/manage runtime behavior
  src/core/extensions/loader.ts,project,module load and import resolution path
docs[2]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/examples/starter-extension/README.md,project,local starter guidance for extension packaging
  docs/EXTENSIONS.md,project,sdk dependency guidance
body: "During sandbox extension lifecycle audit, pm extension doctor reported extension_load_failed for local installs because Node could not resolve @unbrained/pm-cli from extension directory. Need deterministic UX: either improve install/runtime behavior or strengthen diagnostics/docs to make dependency expectations explicit."
